11.01 Mutual Guarantees. Each Party offers the following to the other:
(a) as of the Effective Date:
1. the execution of this Agreement by such Party is consistent with current agreements, and
2. all governmental consents are expected to be obtained;
(b) it attempts to control, in the sense of having the right to license or convey, any Prior Art to be provided to the other Party hereunder, and such Prior Art, in the Disclosing Party's judgement, will not be subject to any encumbrances;
(c) its staff who perform services are under obligation:
(1) not to disclose secret information except as instructed by their employer;
(2) to attempt to assign to their employer all Program Inventions; and
(3) to assign to their employer copyrights to works created in connection with any Project.
